  <title>WebKit2.WebInspector::detach</title>
  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
connect('detach', function (webInspector, ): Boolean);
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Emitted when the inspector is requested to be detached from the window
it is currently attached to. The inspector is detached when the inspector page
is about to be closed, and this signal is emitted right before
<link xref="WebKit2.WebInspector-closed"/>, or when the user clicks on the detach button
in the inspector view to show the inspector in a separate window. In this case
the signal <link xref="WebKit2.WebInspector-open-window"/> is emitted after this one.</p>  <p>To prevent the inspector vew from being detached you can connect to this
signal and simply return <code>true</code>.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>webInspector</code></title>
<p>instance of <link xref="WebKit2.WebInspector"/> that is emitting the signal</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>Returns</code></title>
  <p><code>true</code> to stop other handlers from being invoked for the event.
   <code>false</code> to propagate the event further.</p>
</item>
</terms>

